<LEADPARA>  Two American reporters were wounded Friday while covering a battle between
soldiers and guerrillas in northern El Salvador. Dan Alder, the chief
correspondent in El Salvador for United Press International, and Thomas Long,
a free-lance reporter for the Miami Herald and CBS Radio, were hit by
shrapnel. Long suffered the most serious injury, a chest wound. He was
reported in stable condition. Alder was wounded in the left leg.  </LEADPARA>
